#. <section class="sutta" id="mn138"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "mn138:0.1"
msgid "Majjhima Nikāya 138"
msgstr "Middle Discourses 138"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "mn138:0.2"
msgid "Uddesavibhaṅgasutta"
msgstr "The Analysis of a Recitation Passage"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya1"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.223"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "mn138:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

msgctxt "mn138:1.2"
msgid ""
"ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, "
"Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery."

msgctxt "mn138:1.3"
msgid "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants:"

msgctxt "mn138:1.4"
msgid "“bhikkhavo”ti."
msgstr "“Mendicants!”"

msgctxt "mn138:1.5"
msgid "“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Venerable sir,” they replied."

msgctxt "mn138:1.6"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said this:"

#. <a class="nya" id="nya2"></a>
msgctxt "mn138:2.1"
msgid "“uddesavibhaṅgaṃ vo, bhikkhave, desessāmi."
msgstr "“Mendicants, I shall teach you the analysis of a recitation passage."

msgctxt "mn138:2.2"
msgid "Taṃ suṇātha, sādhukaṃ manasi karotha, bhāsissāmī”ti."
msgstr "Listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”"

msgctxt "mn138:2.3"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” they replied."

msgctxt "mn138:2.4"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said this:"

# For avikkhitta avisata, see AN 4.246. asanthita is curious in this context. Analayo CSMN notes that this reading is opposite in MA. But this would seem to be a normalization, since asanthita is supported by several passages in Iti. In addition to the parallel to the current passage noted by Analayo, it appears in a similar sense in Iti 51 (āruppesu asaṇṭhitā) and Iti 73.
#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya3"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
#. VAR: yathā yathā → yathā yathāssu (bj) | yathā yathāssa (s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "mn138:3.1"
msgid ""
"“Tathā tathā, bhikkhave, bhikkhu upaparikkheyya yathā yathā upaparikkhato "
"bahiddhā cassa viññāṇaṃ avikkhittaṃ avisaṭaṃ, ajjhattaṃ asaṇṭhitaṃ anupādāya "
"na paritasseyya."
msgstr ""
"“A mendicant should examine in any such a way that their consciousness is "
"neither scattered and diffused externally nor stuck internally, and they are "
"not anxious because of grasping."

msgctxt "mn138:3.2"
msgid ""
"Bahiddhā, bhikkhave, viññāṇe avikkhitte avisaṭe sati ajjhattaṃ asaṇṭhite "
"anupādāya aparitassato āyatiṃ jātijarāmaraṇadukkhasamudayasambhavo na "
"hotī”ti."
msgstr ""
"When this is the case and they are no longer anxious, there is for them no "
"coming to be of the origin of suffering—of rebirth, old age, and death in "
"the future.”"

#. <a class="nya" id="nya4"></a>
msgctxt "mn138:4.1"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā."
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said."

msgctxt "mn138:4.2"
msgid "Idaṃ vatvāna sugato uṭṭhāyāsanā vihāraṃ pāvisi."
msgstr ""
"When he had spoken, the Holy One got up from his seat and entered his "
"dwelling."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya5"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.224"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "mn138:5.1"
msgid "Atha kho tesaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ, acirapakkantassa bhagavato, etadahosi:"
msgstr "Soon after the Buddha left, those mendicants considered:"

msgctxt "mn138:5.2"
msgid ""
"“idaṃ kho no, āvuso, bhagavā saṅkhittena uddesaṃ uddisitvā vitthārena atthaṃ "
"avibhajitvā uṭṭhāyāsanā vihāraṃ paviṭṭho:"
msgstr ""
"“The Buddha gave this brief passage for recitation, then entered his "
"dwelling without explaining the meaning in detail."

msgctxt "mn138:5.3"
msgid ""
"‘tathā tathā, bhikkhave, bhikkhu upaparikkheyya yathā yathā upaparikkhato "
"bahiddhā cassa viññāṇaṃ avikkhittaṃ avisaṭaṃ, ajjhattaṃ asaṇṭhitaṃ anupādāya "
"na paritasseyya."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn138:5.4"
msgid ""
"Bahiddhā, bhikkhave, viññāṇe avikkhitte avisaṭe sati ajjhattaṃ asaṇṭhite "
"anupādāya aparitassato āyatiṃ jātijarāmaraṇadukkhasamudayasambhavo na "
"hotī’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn138:5.5"
msgid ""
"Ko nu kho imassa bhagavatā saṅkhittena uddesassa uddiṭṭhassa vitthārena "
"atthaṃ avibhattassa vitthārena atthaṃ vibhajeyyā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"Who can explain in detail the meaning of this brief passage for recitation "
"given by the Buddha?”"

msgctxt "mn138:5.6"
msgid "Atha kho tesaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then those mendicants thought:"

msgctxt "mn138:5.7"
msgid ""
"“ayaṃ kho āyasmā mahākaccāno satthu ceva saṃvaṇṇito sambhāvito ca viññūnaṃ "
"sabrahmacārīnaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"“This Venerable Mahākaccāna is praised by the Buddha and esteemed by his "
"sensible spiritual companions."

msgctxt "mn138:5.8"
msgid ""
"pahoti cāyasmā mahākaccāno imassa bhagavatā saṅkhittena uddesassa "
"uddiṭṭhassa vitthārena atthaṃ avibhattassa vitthārena atthaṃ vibhajituṃ."
msgstr ""
"He is capable of explaining in detail the meaning of this brief passage for "
"recitation given by the Buddha."

msgctxt "mn138:5.9"
msgid ""
"Yannūna mayaṃ yenāyasmā mahākaccāno tenupasaṅkameyyāma; upasaṅkamitvā "
"āyasmantaṃ mahākaccānaṃ etamatthaṃ paṭipuccheyyāmā”ti."
msgstr "Let’s go to him, and ask him about this matter.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya6"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "mn138:6.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho te bhikkhū yenāyasmā mahākaccāno tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā "
"āyasmatā mahākaccānena saddhiṃ sammodiṃsu."
msgstr ""
"Then those mendicants went to Mahākaccāna, and exchanged greetings with him."

msgctxt "mn138:6.2"
msgid ""
"Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ "
"nisinnā kho te bhikkhū āyasmantaṃ mahākaccānaṃ etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr ""
"When the greetings and polite conversation were over, they sat down to one "
"side. They told him what had happened, and said:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "mn138:6.3"
msgid ""
"“Idaṃ kho no, āvuso kaccāna, bhagavā saṅkhittena uddesaṃ uddisitvā "
"vitthārena atthaṃ avibhajitvā uṭṭhāyāsanā vihāraṃ paviṭṭho:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn138:6.4"
msgid ""
"‘tathā tathā, bhikkhave, bhikkhu upaparikkheyya yathā yathā upaparikkhato "
"bahiddhā cassa viññāṇaṃ avikkhittaṃ avisaṭaṃ, ajjhattaṃ asaṇṭhitaṃ anupādāya "
"na paritasseyya."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn138:6.5"
msgid ""
"Bahiddhā, bhikkhave, viññāṇe avikkhitte avisaṭe sati ajjhattaṃ asaṇṭhite "
"anupādāya aparitassato āyatiṃ jātijarāmaraṇadukkhasamudayasambhavo na "
"hotī’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn138:6.6"
msgid ""
"Tesaṃ no, āvuso kaccāna, amhākaṃ, acirapakkantassa bhagavato, etadahosi:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn138:6.7"
msgid ""
"‘idaṃ kho no, āvuso, bhagavā saṅkhittena uddesaṃ uddisitvā vitthārena atthaṃ "
"avibhajitvā uṭṭhāyāsanā vihāraṃ paviṭṭho:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn138:6.8"
msgid ""
"“tathā tathā, bhikkhave, bhikkhu upaparikkheyya, yathā yathā upaparikkhato "
"bahiddhā cassa viññāṇaṃ avikkhittaṃ avisaṭaṃ ajjhattaṃ asaṇṭhitaṃ anupādāya "
"na paritasseyya."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn138:6.9"
msgid ""
"Bahiddhā, bhikkhave, viññāṇe avikkhitte avisaṭe sati ajjhattaṃ asaṇṭhite "
"anupādāya aparitassato āyatiṃ jātijarāmaraṇadukkhasamudayasambhavo na "
"hotī”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn138:6.10"
msgid ""
"Ko nu kho imassa bhagavatā saṅkhittena uddesassa uddiṭṭhassa vitthārena "
"atthaṃ avibhattassa vitthārena atthaṃ vibhajeyyā’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn138:6.11"
msgid "Tesaṃ no, āvuso kaccāna, amhākaṃ etadahosi:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn138:6.12"
msgid ""
"‘ayaṃ kho āyasmā mahākaccāno satthu ceva saṃvaṇṇito, sambhāvito ca viññūnaṃ "
"sabrahmacārīnaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn138:6.13"
msgid ""
"Pahoti cāyasmā mahākaccāno imassa bhagavatā saṅkhittena uddesassa "
"uddiṭṭhassa vitthārena atthaṃ avibhattassa vitthārena atthaṃ vibhajituṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn138:6.14"
msgid ""
"Yannūna mayaṃ yenāyasmā mahākaccāno tenupasaṅkameyyāma; upasaṅkamitvā "
"āyasmantaṃ mahākaccānaṃ etamatthaṃ paṭipuccheyyāmā’ti—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn138:6.15"
msgid "vibhajatāyasmā mahākaccāno”ti."
msgstr "“May Venerable Mahākaccāna please explain this.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya7"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.225"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "mn138:7.1"
msgid ""
"“Seyyathāpi, āvuso, puriso sāratthiko sāragavesī sārapariyesanaṃ caramāno "
"mahato rukkhassa tiṭṭhato sāravato atikkammeva mūlaṃ atikkamma khandhaṃ "
"sākhāpalāse sāraṃ pariyesitabbaṃ maññeyya, "
msgstr ""
"“Reverends, suppose there was a person in need of heartwood. And while "
"wandering in search of heartwood he’d come across a large tree standing with "
"heartwood. But he’d pass over the roots and trunk, imagining that the "
"heartwood should be sought in the branches and leaves. "

msgctxt "mn138:7.2"
msgid ""
"evaṃ sampadamidaṃ āyasmantānaṃ satthari sammukhībhūte taṃ bhagavantaṃ "
"atisitvā amhe etamatthaṃ paṭipucchitabbaṃ maññatha."
msgstr ""
"Such is the consequence for the venerables. Though you were face to face "
"with the Buddha, you passed him by, imagining that you should ask me about "
"this matter."

msgctxt "mn138:7.3"
msgid ""
"So hāvuso, bhagavā jānaṃ jānāti, passaṃ passati, cakkhubhūto ñāṇabhūto "
"dhammabhūto brahmabhūto vattā pavattā atthassa ninnetā amatassa dātā "
"dhammassāmī tathāgato."
msgstr ""
"For he is the Buddha, who knows and sees. He is vision, he is knowledge, he "
"is the truth, he is supreme. He is the teacher, the proclaimer, the "
"elucidator of meaning, the bestower of the deathless, the lord of truth, the "
"Realized One."

msgctxt "mn138:7.4"
msgid ""
"So ceva panetassa kālo ahosi yaṃ bhagavantaṃyeva etamatthaṃ paṭipuccheyyātha;"
msgstr "That was the time to approach the Buddha and ask about this matter."

msgctxt "mn138:7.5"
msgid "yathā vo bhagavā byākareyya tathā naṃ dhāreyyāthā”ti."
msgstr "You should have remembered it in line with the Buddha’s answer.”"

#. <a class="nya" id="nya8"></a>
msgctxt "mn138:8.1"
msgid ""
"“Addhāvuso kaccāna, bhagavā jānaṃ jānāti, passaṃ passati, cakkhubhūto "
"ñāṇabhūto dhammabhūto brahmabhūto vattā pavattā atthassa ninnetā amatassa "
"dātā dhammassāmī tathāgato."
msgstr ""
"“Certainly he is the Buddha, who knows and sees. He is vision, he is "
"knowledge, he is the truth, he is supreme. He is the teacher, the "
"proclaimer, the elucidator of meaning, the bestower of the deathless, the "
"lord of truth, the Realized One."

msgctxt "mn138:8.2"
msgid ""
"So ceva panetassa kālo ahosi yaṃ bhagavantaṃyeva etamatthaṃ paṭipuccheyyāma;"
msgstr "That was the time to approach the Buddha and ask about this matter."

msgctxt "mn138:8.3"
msgid "yathā no bhagavā byākareyya tathā naṃ dhāreyyāma."
msgstr "We should have remembered it in line with the Buddha’s answer."

msgctxt "mn138:8.4"
msgid ""
"Api cāyasmā mahākaccāno satthu ceva saṃvaṇṇito sambhāvito ca viññūnaṃ "
"sabrahmacārīnaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Still, Venerable Mahākaccāna is praised by the Buddha and esteemed by his "
"sensible spiritual companions."

msgctxt "mn138:8.5"
msgid ""
"Pahoti cāyasmā mahākaccāno imassa bhagavatā saṅkhittena uddesassa "
"uddiṭṭhassa vitthārena atthaṃ avibhattassa vitthārena atthaṃ vibhajituṃ."
msgstr ""
"He is capable of explaining in detail the meaning of this brief passage for "
"recitation given by the Buddha."

msgctxt "mn138:8.6"
msgid "Vibhajatāyasmā mahākaccāno agaruṃ karitvā”ti."
msgstr "Please explain this, if it’s no trouble.”"

#. <a class="nya" id="nya9"></a>
msgctxt "mn138:9.1"
msgid "“Tena hāvuso, suṇātha, sādhukaṃ manasi karotha, bhāsissāmī”ti."
msgstr "“Well then, reverends, listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”"

msgctxt "mn138:9.2"
msgid "“Evamāvuso”ti kho te bhikkhū āyasmato mahākaccānassa paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Yes, reverend,” they replied."

msgctxt "mn138:9.3"
msgid "Āyasmā mahākaccāno etadavoca:"
msgstr "Venerable Mahākaccāna said this:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "mn138:9.4"
msgid ""
"“Yaṃ kho no, āvuso, bhagavā saṅkhittena uddesaṃ uddisitvā vitthārena atthaṃ "
"avibhajitvā uṭṭhāyāsanā vihāraṃ paviṭṭho:"
msgstr ""
"“Reverends, the Buddha gave this brief passage for recitation, then entered "
"his dwelling without explaining the meaning in detail:"

msgctxt "mn138:9.5"
msgid ""
"‘tathā tathā, bhikkhave, bhikkhu upaparikkheyya, yathā yathā upaparikkhato "
"bahiddhā cassa viññāṇaṃ avikkhittaṃ avisaṭaṃ ajjhattaṃ asaṇṭhitaṃ anupādāya "
"na paritasseyya, bahiddhā, bhikkhave, viññāṇe avikkhitte avisaṭe sati "
"ajjhattaṃ asaṇṭhite anupādāya aparitassato āyatiṃ "
"jātijarāmaraṇadukkhasamudayasambhavo na hotī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘A mendicant should examine in any such a way that their consciousness is "
"neither scattered and diffused externally nor stuck internally, and they are "
"not anxious because of grasping. When this is the case and they are no "
"longer anxious, there is for them no coming to be of the origin of suffering—"
"of rebirth, old age, and death in the future.’"

msgctxt "mn138:9.6"
msgid ""
"Imassa kho ahaṃ, āvuso, bhagavatā saṅkhittena uddesassa uddiṭṭhassa "
"vitthārena atthaṃ avibhattassa evaṃ vitthārena atthaṃ ājānāmi."
msgstr ""
"And this is how I understand the detailed meaning of this passage for "
"recitation."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya10"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "mn138:10.1"
msgid "Kathañcāvuso, bahiddhā viññāṇaṃ vikkhittaṃ visaṭanti vuccati?"
msgstr "And how is consciousness scattered and diffused externally?"

# nimitta here is obviously related to the basic sense restraint passage: cakkhunā rūpaṃ disvā na nimittaggāhī hoti nānubyañjanaggāhī.
msgctxt "mn138:10.2"
msgid ""
"Idhāvuso, bhikkhuno cakkhunā rūpaṃ disvā rūpanimittānusāri viññāṇaṃ hoti "
"rūpanimittassādagadhitaṃ rūpanimittassādavinibandhaṃ "
"rūpanimittassādasaṃyojanasaṃyuttaṃ bahiddhā viññāṇaṃ vikkhittaṃ visaṭanti "
"vuccati."
msgstr ""
"Take a mendicant who sees a sight with their eyes. Their consciousness "
"follows after the features of that sight, tied, attached, and fettered to "
"gratification in its features. So their consciousness is said to be "
"scattered and diffused externally."

msgctxt "mn138:10.3"
msgid "Sotena saddaṃ sutvā … pe …"
msgstr "When they hear a sound with their ears …"

msgctxt "mn138:10.4"
msgid "ghānena gandhaṃ ghāyitvā …"
msgstr "When they smell an odor with their nose …"

msgctxt "mn138:10.5"
msgid "jivhāya rasaṃ sāyitvā …"
msgstr "When they taste a flavor with their tongue …"

msgctxt "mn138:10.6"
msgid "kāyena phoṭṭhabbaṃ phusitvā …"
msgstr "When they feel a touch with their body …"

msgctxt "mn138:10.7"
msgid ""
"manasā dhammaṃ viññāya dhammanimittānusāri viññāṇaṃ hoti; "
"dhammanimittassādagadhitaṃ dhammanimittassādavinibandhaṃ "
"dhammanimittassādasaṃyojanasaṃyuttaṃ bahiddhā viññāṇaṃ vikkhittaṃ visaṭanti "
"vuccati."
msgstr ""
"When they know a thought with their mind, their consciousness follows after "
"the features of that thought, tied, attached, and fettered to gratification "
"in its features. So their consciousness is said to be scattered and diffused "
"externally."

msgctxt "mn138:10.8"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, āvuso, bahiddhā viññāṇaṃ vikkhittaṃ visaṭanti vuccati."
msgstr "That’s how consciousness is scattered and diffused externally."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya11"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.226"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "mn138:11.1"
msgid "Kathañcāvuso, bahiddhā viññāṇaṃ avikkhittaṃ avisaṭanti vuccati?"
msgstr "And how is consciousness not scattered and diffused externally?"

msgctxt "mn138:11.2"
msgid ""
"Idhāvuso, bhikkhuno cakkhunā rūpaṃ disvā na rūpanimittānusāri viññāṇaṃ hoti, "
"na rūpanimittassādagadhitaṃ na rūpanimittassādavinibandhaṃ na "
"rūpanimittassādasaṃyojanasaṃyuttaṃ bahiddhā viññāṇaṃ avikkhittaṃ avisaṭanti "
"vuccati."
msgstr ""
"Take a mendicant who sees a sight with their eyes. Their consciousness doesn’"
"t follow after the features of that sight, and is not tied, attached, and "
"fettered to gratification in its features. So their consciousness is said to "
"be not scattered and diffused externally."

msgctxt "mn138:11.3"
msgid "Sotena saddaṃ sutvā … pe …"
msgstr "When they hear a sound with their ears …"

msgctxt "mn138:11.4"
msgid "ghānena gandhaṃ ghāyitvā …"
msgstr "When they smell an odor with their nose …"

msgctxt "mn138:11.5"
msgid "jivhāya rasaṃ sāyitvā …"
msgstr "When they taste a flavor with their tongue …"

msgctxt "mn138:11.6"
msgid "kāyena phoṭṭhabbaṃ phusitvā …"
msgstr "When they feel a touch with their body …"

msgctxt "mn138:11.7"
msgid ""
"manasā dhammaṃ viññāya na dhammanimittānusāri viññāṇaṃ hoti na "
"dhammanimittassādagadhitaṃ na dhammanimittassādavinibandhaṃ na "
"dhammanimittassādasaṃyojanasaṃyuttaṃ bahiddhā viññāṇaṃ avikkhittaṃ "
"avisaṭanti vuccati."
msgstr ""
"When they know a thought with their mind, their consciousness doesn’t follow "
"after the features of that thought, and is not tied, attached, and fettered "
"to gratification in its features. So their consciousness is said to be not "
"scattered and diffused externally."

msgctxt "mn138:11.8"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, āvuso, bahiddhā viññāṇaṃ avikkhittaṃ avisaṭanti vuccati."
msgstr "That’s how consciousness is not scattered and diffused externally."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya12"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
#. VAR: ajjhattaṃ → ajjhattaṃ cittaṃ (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "mn138:12.1"
msgid "Kathañcāvuso, ajjhattaṃ saṇṭhitanti vuccati?"
msgstr "And how is their consciousness stuck internally?"

msgctxt "mn138:12.2"
msgid ""
"Idhāvuso, bhikkhu vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi savitakkaṃ "
"savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"Take a mendicant who, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from "
"unskillful qualities, enters and remains in the first absorption, which has "
"the rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping "
"it connected."

msgctxt "mn138:12.3"
msgid ""
"Tassa vivekajapītisukhānusāri viññāṇaṃ hoti vivekajapītisukhassādagadhitaṃ "
"vivekajapītisukhassādavinibandhaṃ vivekajapītisukhassādasaṃyojanasaṃyuttaṃ "
"ajjhattaṃ cittaṃ saṇṭhitanti vuccati."
msgstr ""
"Their consciousness follows after that rapture and bliss born of seclusion, "
"tied, attached, and fettered to gratification in that rapture and bliss born "
"of seclusion. So their mind is said to be stuck internally."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya13"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "mn138:13.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā ajjhattaṃ "
"sampasādanaṃ cetaso ekodibhāvaṃ avitakkaṃ avicāraṃ samādhijaṃ pītisukhaṃ "
"dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, as the placing of the mind and keeping it connected are "
"stilled, a mendicant enters and remains in the second absorption, which has "
"the rapture and bliss born of immersion, with internal clarity and "
"confidence, and unified mind, without placing the mind and keeping it "
"connected."

msgctxt "mn138:13.2"
msgid ""
"Tassa samādhijapītisukhānusāri viññāṇaṃ hoti samādhijapītisukhassādagadhitaṃ "
"samādhijapītisukhassādavinibandhaṃ samādhijapītisukhassādasaṃyojanasaṃyuttaṃ "
"ajjhattaṃ cittaṃ saṇṭhitanti vuccati."
msgstr ""
"Their consciousness follows after that rapture and bliss born of immersion, "
"tied, attached, and fettered to gratification in that rapture and bliss born "
"of immersion. So their mind is said to be stuck internally."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya14"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "mn138:14.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu pītiyā ca virāgā upekkhako ca viharati sato ca "
"sampajāno sukhañca kāyena paṭisaṃvedeti, yaṃ taṃ ariyā ācikkhanti: ‘"
"upekkhako satimā sukhavihārī’ti tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, with the fading away of rapture, a mendicant enters and remains "
"in the third absorption, where they meditate with equanimity, mindful and "
"aware, personally experiencing the bliss of which the noble ones declare, ‘"
"Equanimous and mindful, one meditates in bliss.’"

# text has upekkha in the first case, upekkhasukha subsequently, with apparently no vll. because of the way he abbreviates, BB’s translation doesn’t show this difference.
msgctxt "mn138:14.2"
msgid ""
"Tassa upekkhānusāri viññāṇaṃ hoti upekkhāsukhassādagadhitaṃ "
"upekkhāsukhassādavinibandhaṃ upekkhāsukhassādasaṃyojanasaṃyuttaṃ ajjhattaṃ "
"cittaṃ saṇṭhitanti vuccati."
msgstr ""
"Their consciousness follows after that equanimity, tied, attached, and "
"fettered to gratification in that equanimous bliss. So their mind is said to "
"be stuck internally."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya15"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
msgctxt "mn138:15.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu sukhassa ca pahānā dukkhassa ca pahānā pubbeva "
"somanassadomanassānaṃ atthaṅgamā adukkhamasukhaṃ upekkhāsatipārisuddhiṃ "
"catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, giving up pleasure and pain, and ending former happiness and "
"sadness, a mendicant enters and remains in the fourth absorption, without "
"pleasure or pain, with pure equanimity and mindfulness."

#. VAR: ajjhattaṃ → ajjhattaṃ cittaṃ (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "mn138:15.2"
msgid ""
"Tassa adukkhamasukhānusāri viññāṇaṃ hoti adukkhamasukhassādagadhitaṃ "
"adukkhamasukhassādavinibandhaṃ adukkhamasukhassādasaṃyojanasaṃyuttaṃ "
"ajjhattaṃ cittaṃ asaṇṭhitanti vuccati."
msgstr ""
"Their consciousness follows after that neutral feeling, tied, attached, and "
"fettered to gratification in that neutral feeling. So their mind is said to "
"be stuck internally."

msgctxt "mn138:15.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, āvuso, ajjhattaṃ saṇṭhitanti vuccati."
msgstr "That’s how their consciousness is stuck internally."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya16"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.227"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc14"></a>
#. VAR: ajjhattaṃ → ajjhattaṃ cittaṃ (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "mn138:16.1"
msgid "Kathañcāvuso, ajjhattaṃ asaṇṭhitanti vuccati?"
msgstr "And how is their consciousness not stuck internally?"

msgctxt "mn138:16.2"
msgid ""
"Idhāvuso, bhikkhu vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi … pe … "
"paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from "
"unskillful qualities, enters and remains in the first absorption, which has "
"the rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping "
"it connected."

msgctxt "mn138:16.3"
msgid ""
"Tassa na vivekajapītisukhānusāri viññāṇaṃ hoti na "
"vivekajapītisukhassādagadhitaṃ na vivekajapītisukhassādavinibandhaṃ na "
"vivekajapītisukhassādasaṃyojanasaṃyuttaṃ ajjhattaṃ cittaṃ asaṇṭhitanti "
"vuccati."
msgstr ""
"Their consciousness doesn’t follow after that rapture and bliss born of "
"seclusion, and is not tied, attached, and fettered to gratification in that "
"rapture and bliss born of seclusion. So their mind is said to be not stuck "
"internally."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya17"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc15"></a>
msgctxt "mn138:17.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā … pe … dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ "
"upasampajja viharati."
msgstr "Furthermore, they enter the second absorption …"

msgctxt "mn138:17.2"
msgid ""
"Tassa na samādhijapītisukhānusāri viññāṇaṃ hoti na "
"samādhijapītisukhassādagadhitaṃ na samādhijapītisukhassādavinibandhaṃ na "
"samādhijapītisukhassādasaṃyojanasaṃyuttaṃ ajjhattaṃ cittaṃ asaṇṭhitanti "
"vuccati."
msgstr ""
"Their consciousness doesn’t follow after that rapture and bliss born of "
"immersion …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya18"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc16"></a>
msgctxt "mn138:18.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu pītiyā ca virāgā … pe … tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ "
"upasampajja viharati."
msgstr "Furthermore, they enter and remain in the third absorption …"

msgctxt "mn138:18.2"
msgid ""
"Tassa na upekkhānusāri viññāṇaṃ hoti na upekkhāsukhassādagadhitaṃ na "
"upekkhāsukhassādavinibandhaṃ na upekkhāsukhassādasaṃyojanasaṃyuttaṃ "
"ajjhattaṃ cittaṃ asaṇṭhitanti vuccati."
msgstr ""
"Their consciousness doesn’t follow after that equanimity, and is not tied, "
"attached, and fettered to gratification in that equanimous bliss. So their "
"mind is said to be not stuck internally."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya19"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc17"></a>
msgctxt "mn138:19.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu sukhassa ca pahānā dukkhassa ca pahānā pubbeva "
"somanassadomanassānaṃ atthaṅgamā adukkhamasukhaṃ upekkhāsatipārisuddhiṃ "
"catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr "Furthermore, they enter and remain in the fourth absorption …"

#. VAR: ajjhattaṃ → ajjhattaṃ cittaṃ (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "mn138:19.2"
msgid ""
"Tassa na adukkhamasukhānusāri viññāṇaṃ hoti na adukkhamasukhassādagadhitaṃ "
"na adukkhamasukhassādavinibandhaṃ na adukkhamasukhassādasaṃyojanasaṃyuttaṃ "
"ajjhattaṃ cittaṃ asaṇṭhitanti vuccati."
msgstr ""
"Their consciousness doesn’t follow after that neutral feeling, and is not "
"tied, attached, and fettered to gratification in that neutral feeling. So "
"their mind is said to be not stuck internally."

msgctxt "mn138:19.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, āvuso, ajjhattaṃ asaṇṭhitanti vuccati."
msgstr "That’s how their consciousness is not stuck internally."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya20"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.228"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc18"></a>
msgctxt "mn138:20.1"
msgid "Kathañcāvuso, anupādā paritassanā hoti?"
msgstr "And how are they anxious because of grasping?"

msgctxt "mn138:20.2"
msgid ""
"Idhāvuso, assutavā puthujjano ariyānaṃ adassāvī ariyadhammassa akovido "
"ariyadhamme avinīto sappurisānaṃ adassāvī sappurisadhammassa akovido "
"sappurisadhamme avinīto "
msgstr ""
"It’s when an uneducated ordinary person has not seen the noble ones, and is "
"neither skilled nor trained in the teaching of the noble ones. They’ve not "
"seen good persons, and are neither skilled nor trained in the teaching of "
"the good persons. "

msgctxt "mn138:20.3"
msgid ""
"rūpaṃ attato samanupassati rūpavantaṃ vā attānaṃ attani vā rūpaṃ rūpasmiṃ vā "
"attānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"They regard form as self, self as having form, form in self, or self in form."

msgctxt "mn138:20.4"
msgid "Tassa taṃ rūpaṃ vipariṇamati, aññathā hoti."
msgstr "But that form of theirs decays and perishes,"

msgctxt "mn138:20.5"
msgid ""
"Tassa rūpavipariṇāmaññathābhāvā rūpavipariṇāmānuparivatti viññāṇaṃ hoti."
msgstr "and consciousness latches on to the perishing of form."

msgctxt "mn138:20.6"
msgid ""
"Tassa rūpavipariṇāmānuparivattajā paritassanā dhammasamuppādā cittaṃ "
"pariyādāya tiṭṭhanti."
msgstr ""
"Anxieties occupy their mind, born of latching on to the perishing of form, "
"and originating in accordance with natural principles."

msgctxt "mn138:20.7"
msgid ""
"Cetaso pariyādānā uttāsavā ca hoti vighātavā ca apekkhavā ca anupādāya ca "
"paritassati."
msgstr ""
"So they become frightened, worried, concerned, and anxious because of "
"grasping."

msgctxt "mn138:20.8"
msgid "Vedanaṃ … pe …"
msgstr "They regard feeling …"

msgctxt "mn138:20.9"
msgid "saññaṃ …"
msgstr "perception …"

msgctxt "mn138:20.10"
msgid "saṅkhāre …"
msgstr "choices …"

msgctxt "mn138:20.11"
msgid ""
"viññāṇaṃ attato samanupassati viññāṇavantaṃ vā attānaṃ attani vā viññāṇaṃ "
"viññāṇasmiṃ vā attānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"consciousness as self, self as having consciousness, consciousness in self, "
"or self in consciousness."

msgctxt "mn138:20.12"
msgid "Tassa taṃ viññāṇaṃ vipariṇamati, aññathā hoti."
msgstr "But that consciousness of theirs decays and perishes,"

msgctxt "mn138:20.13"
msgid ""
"Tassa viññāṇavipariṇāmaññathābhāvā viññāṇavipariṇāmānuparivatti viññāṇaṃ "
"hoti."
msgstr "and consciousness latches on to the perishing of consciousness."

msgctxt "mn138:20.14"
msgid ""
"Tassa viññāṇavipariṇāmānuparivattajā paritassanā dhammasamuppādā cittaṃ "
"pariyādāya tiṭṭhanti."
msgstr ""
"Anxieties occupy their mind, born of latching on to the perishing of "
"consciousness, and originating in accordance with natural principles."

msgctxt "mn138:20.15"
msgid ""
"Cetaso pariyādānā uttāsavā ca hoti vighātavā ca apekkhavā ca anupādāya ca "
"paritassati."
msgstr ""
"So they become frightened, worried, concerned, and anxious because of "
"grasping."

msgctxt "mn138:20.16"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, āvuso, anupādā paritassanā hoti."
msgstr "That’s how they are anxious because of grasping."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya21"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc19"></a>
msgctxt "mn138:21.1"
msgid "Kathañcāvuso, anupādānā aparitassanā hoti?"
msgstr "And how are they not anxious because of grasping?"

msgctxt "mn138:21.2"
msgid ""
"Idhāvuso, sutavā ariyasāvako ariyānaṃ dassāvī ariyadhammassa kovido "
"ariyadhamme suvinīto sappurisānaṃ dassāvī sappurisadhammassa kovido "
"sappurisadhamme suvinīto "
msgstr ""
"It’s when an educated noble disciple has seen the noble ones, and is skilled "
"and trained in the teaching of the noble ones. They’ve seen good persons, "
"and are skilled and trained in the teaching of the good persons. "

msgctxt "mn138:21.3"
msgid ""
"na rūpaṃ attato samanupassati na rūpavantaṃ vā attānaṃ na attani vā rūpaṃ na "
"rūpasmiṃ vā attānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"They don’t regard form as self, self as having form, form in self, or self "
"in form."

msgctxt "mn138:21.4"
msgid "Tassa taṃ rūpaṃ vipariṇamati, aññathā hoti."
msgstr "When that form of theirs decays and perishes,"

msgctxt "mn138:21.5"
msgid ""
"Tassa rūpavipariṇāmaññathābhāvā na ca rūpavipariṇāmānuparivatti viññāṇaṃ "
"hoti."
msgstr "consciousness doesn’t latch on to the perishing of form."

msgctxt "mn138:21.6"
msgid ""
"Tassa na rūpavipariṇāmānuparivattajā paritassanā dhammasamuppādā cittaṃ "
"pariyādāya tiṭṭhanti."
msgstr ""
"Anxieties—born of latching on to the perishing of form and originating in "
"accordance with natural principles—don’t occupy their mind."

#. VAR: na cevuttāsavā → na ceva uttāsavā (bj, s1-3)
msgctxt "mn138:21.7"
msgid ""
"Cetaso pariyādānā na cevuttāsavā hoti na ca vighātavā na ca apekkhavā "
"anupādāya ca na paritassati."
msgstr ""
"So they don’t become frightened, worried, concerned, or anxious because of "
"grasping."

msgctxt "mn138:21.8"
msgid "Na vedanaṃ …"
msgstr "They don’t regard feeling …"

msgctxt "mn138:21.9"
msgid "na saññaṃ …"
msgstr "perception …"

msgctxt "mn138:21.10"
msgid "na saṅkhāre …"
msgstr "choices …"

msgctxt "mn138:21.11"
msgid ""
"na viññāṇaṃ attato samanupassati na viññāṇavantaṃ vā attānaṃ na attani vā "
"viññāṇaṃ na viññāṇasmiṃ vā attānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"consciousness as self, self as having consciousness, consciousness in self, "
"or self in consciousness."

msgctxt "mn138:21.12"
msgid "Tassa taṃ viññāṇaṃ vipariṇamati, aññathā hoti."
msgstr "When that consciousness of theirs decays and perishes,"

msgctxt "mn138:21.13"
msgid ""
"Tassa viññāṇavipariṇāmaññathābhāvā na ca viññāṇavipariṇāmānuparivatti "
"viññāṇaṃ hoti."
msgstr "consciousness doesn’t latch on to the perishing of consciousness."

msgctxt "mn138:21.14"
msgid ""
"Tassa na viññāṇavipariṇāmānuparivattajā paritassanā dhammasamuppādā cittaṃ "
"pariyādāya tiṭṭhanti."
msgstr ""
"Anxieties—born of latching on to the perishing of consciousness and "
"originating in accordance with natural principles—don’t occupy their mind."

msgctxt "mn138:21.15"
msgid ""
"Cetaso pariyādānā na cevuttāsavā hoti na ca vighātavā na ca apekkhavā, "
"anupādāya ca na paritassati."
msgstr ""
"So they don’t become frightened, worried, concerned, or anxious because of "
"grasping."

msgctxt "mn138:21.16"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, āvuso, anupādā aparitassanā hoti."
msgstr "That’s how they are not anxious because of grasping."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya22"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.229"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc20"></a>
msgctxt "mn138:22.1"
msgid ""
"Yaṃ kho no, āvuso, bhagavā saṅkhittena uddesaṃ uddisitvā vitthārena atthaṃ "
"avibhajitvā uṭṭhāyāsanā vihāraṃ paviṭṭho:"
msgstr ""
"The Buddha gave this brief passage for recitation, then entered his dwelling "
"without explaining the meaning in detail:"

msgctxt "mn138:22.2"
msgid ""
"‘tathā tathā, bhikkhave, bhikkhu upaparikkheyya yathā yathā upaparikkhato "
"bahiddhā cassa viññāṇaṃ avikkhittaṃ avisaṭaṃ, ajjhattaṃ asaṇṭhitaṃ anupādāya "
"na paritasseyya."
msgstr ""
"‘A mendicant should examine in any such a way that their consciousness is "
"neither scattered and diffused externally nor stuck internally, and they are "
"not anxious because of grasping."

msgctxt "mn138:22.3"
msgid ""
"Bahiddhā, bhikkhave, viññāṇe avikkhitte avisaṭe sati ajjhattaṃ asaṇṭhite "
"anupādāya aparitassato āyatiṃ jātijarāmaraṇadukkhasamudayasambhavo na "
"hotī’ti."
msgstr ""
"When this is the case and they are no longer anxious, there is for them no "
"coming to be of the origin of suffering—of rebirth, old age, and death in "
"the future.’"

msgctxt "mn138:22.4"
msgid ""
"Imassa kho ahaṃ, āvuso, bhagavatā saṅkhittena uddesassa uddiṭṭhassa "
"vitthārena atthaṃ avibhattassa evaṃ vitthārena atthaṃ ājānāmi."
msgstr ""
"And this is how I understand the detailed meaning of this passage for "
"recitation."

msgctxt "mn138:22.5"
msgid ""
"Ākaṅkhamānā ca pana tumhe āyasmanto bhagavantaṃyeva upasaṅkamitvā etamatthaṃ "
"paṭipuccheyyātha;"
msgstr "If you wish, you may go to the Buddha and ask him about this."

msgctxt "mn138:22.6"
msgid "yathā vo bhagavā byākaroti tathā naṃ dhāreyyāthā”ti."
msgstr "You should remember it in line with the Buddha’s answer.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya23"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc21"></a>
msgctxt "mn138:23.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho te bhikkhū āyasmato mahākaccānassa bhāsitaṃ abhinanditvā anumoditvā "
"uṭṭhāyāsanā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ "
"abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho te bhikkhū "
"bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr ""
"“Yes, reverend,” said those mendicants, approving and agreeing with what "
"Mahākaccāna said. Then they rose from their seats and went to the Buddha, "
"bowed, sat down to one side, and told him what had happened, saying:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc22"></a>
msgctxt "mn138:23.2"
msgid ""
"“Yaṃ kho no, bhante, bhagavā saṅkhittena uddesaṃ uddisitvā vitthārena atthaṃ "
"avibhajitvā uṭṭhāyāsanā vihāraṃ paviṭṭho:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn138:23.3"
msgid ""
"‘tathā tathā, bhikkhave, bhikkhu upaparikkheyya yathā yathā upaparikkhato "
"bahiddhā cassa viññāṇaṃ avikkhittaṃ avisaṭaṃ, ajjhattaṃ asaṇṭhitaṃ anupādāya "
"na paritasseyya."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn138:23.4"
msgid ""
"Bahiddhā, bhikkhave, viññāṇe avikkhitte avisaṭe sati ajjhattaṃ asaṇṭhite "
"anupādāya aparitassato āyatiṃ jātijarāmaraṇadukkhasamudayasambhavo na "
"hotī’ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc23"></a>
msgctxt "mn138:23.5"
msgid "Tesaṃ no, bhante, amhākaṃ, acirapakkantassa bhagavato, etadahosi:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn138:23.6"
msgid ""
"‘idaṃ kho no, āvuso, bhagavā saṅkhittena uddesaṃ uddisitvā vitthārena atthaṃ "
"avibhajitvā uṭṭhāyāsanā vihāraṃ paviṭṭho—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn138:23.7"
msgid ""
"tathā tathā, bhikkhave, bhikkhu upaparikkheyya, yathā yathā upaparikkhato "
"bahiddhā cassa viññāṇaṃ avikkhittaṃ avisaṭaṃ, ajjhattaṃ asaṇṭhitaṃ anupādāya "
"na paritasseyya."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn138:23.8"
msgid ""
"Bahiddhā, bhikkhave, viññāṇe avikkhitte avisaṭe sati ajjhattaṃ asaṇṭhite "
"anupādāya aparitassato āyatiṃ jātijarāmaraṇadukkhasamudayasambhavo na hotīti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn138:23.9"
msgid ""
"Ko nu kho imassa bhagavatā saṅkhittena uddesassa uddiṭṭhassa vitthārena "
"atthaṃ avibhattassa vitthārena atthaṃ vibhajeyyā’ti?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn138:23.10"
msgid "Tesaṃ no, bhante, amhākaṃ etadahosi:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn138:23.11"
msgid ""
"‘ayaṃ kho āyasmā mahākaccāno satthu ceva saṃvaṇṇito sambhāvito ca viññūnaṃ "
"sabrahmacārīnaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn138:23.12"
msgid ""
"Pahoti cāyasmā mahākaccāno imassa bhagavatā saṅkhittena uddesassa "
"uddiṭṭhassa vitthārena atthaṃ avibhattassa vitthārena atthaṃ vibhajituṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn138:23.13"
msgid ""
"Yannūna mayaṃ yenāyasmā mahākaccāno tenupasaṅkameyyāma; upasaṅkamitvā "
"āyasmantaṃ mahākaccānaṃ etamatthaṃ paṭipuccheyyāmā’ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc24"></a>
msgctxt "mn138:23.14"
msgid ""
"Atha kho mayaṃ, bhante, yenāyasmā mahākaccāno tenupasaṅkamimha; "
"upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ mahākaccānaṃ etamatthaṃ paṭipucchimha."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn138:23.15"
msgid ""
"Tesaṃ no, bhante, āyasmatā mahākaccānena imehi ākārehi imehi padehi imehi "
"byañjanehi attho vibhatto”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Mahākaccāna clearly explained the meaning to us in this manner, with these "
"words and phrases.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya24"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc25"></a>
msgctxt "mn138:24.1"
msgid "“Paṇḍito, bhikkhave, mahākaccāno; mahāpañño, bhikkhave, mahākaccāno."
msgstr "“Mahākaccāna is astute, mendicants, he has great wisdom."

msgctxt "mn138:24.2"
msgid ""
"Mañcepi tumhe, bhikkhave, etamatthaṃ paṭipuccheyyātha, ahampi evamevaṃ "
"byākareyyaṃ yathā taṃ mahākaccānena byākataṃ."
msgstr ""
"If you came to me and asked this question, I would answer it in exactly the "
"same way as Mahākaccāna."

#. VAR: cevetassa → eso ceva tassa (s1-3, km) | eso cetassa (pts1) | esoyeva tassa (mr)
msgctxt "mn138:24.3"
msgid "Eso cevetassa attho. Evañca naṃ dhāreyyāthā”ti."
msgstr "That is what it means, and that’s how you should remember it.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc26"></a>
msgctxt "mn138:24.4"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā."
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said."

msgctxt "mn138:24.5"
msgid "Attamanā te bhikkhū bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandunti."
msgstr "Satisfied, the mendicants were happy with what the Buddha said."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "mn138:24.6"
msgid "Uddesavibhaṅgasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ aṭṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
